import React, {useState} from 'react' const Products = () => { const [food, setFood] = useState([{foodName: 'rice', price:50, img:'./rice.jpg', desc:'Sweet Rice buy it'}, {foodName: 'burger', price:20, img:'./rice.jpg', desc:'Sweet Beans buy it'}]) return ( <>

FOOD MENU

{food.map((item, index) => (
{item.foodName}

{item.desc}

Buy ${item.price}
))}
) } export default Products
